Title : Mazda RX-9
Text : {{notability|date=April 2018}}{{speculation|date=April 2018}}
{{For|the LA4 car produced in the 1970s|Mazda Luce#LA4 series (1977â€“1981)}}
The '''Mazda RX-9''' is a [[sports car]] produced by the Japanese automaker [[Mazda]] that is rumored to be slated for release in 2020. ''Holiday Auto'', a Japanese magazine, incorrectly reported  it would be previewed at the 2017 [[Tokyo Auto Show]], and the final production model would be featured at the same event in 2019.<ref name=digitaltrends>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaltrends.com/cars/2020-mazda-rx-9-news-specs-rumors/|first=Ronan|last=Glon|title=The Rotary-Engined Mazda Sports Car Isn't Dead Yet|date=August 24, 2016|publisher=[[Digital Trends]]|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref>  However, it was not shown at the 2017 event.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://jalopnik.com/mazda-is-the-hero-of-the-2017-tokyo-motor-show-1819835255|title=Mazda Is The Hero Of The 2017 Tokyo Motor Show|last=Saito|first=Ken|work=Jalopnik|access-date=2018-04-04|language=en-US}}</ref>

As of 2016, rumors called for the car to be released in January 2020, to coincide with Mazda's 100th anniversary, and would be initially priced at eight million yen (US${{To USD|8000000|JPN|year=2014|round=yes}} in 2015).<ref name=digitaltrends/><ref name=motoring>{{cite web|url=http://www.motoring.com.au/mazda-rx-9-locked-in-103563/|title=Mazda RX-9 locked in|publisher=Motoring|date=August 24, 2016|first=Marton|last=Pettendy|accessdate=August 26, 2016}}</ref> It was believed it will showcase the return of the [[Wankel rotary engine]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.yahoo.com/news/does-mazda-400-hp-rx-123000096.html|title=Does Mazda Have a 400-HP RX-9 In the Works for 2019?|access-date=August 28, 2016}}</ref> but CEO Masamichi Kogai said Mazda will not launch another rotary engine.

